

To install and configure a CASE tool (StarUML / Visual Paradigm) for designing and modeling a Predictive Stock Management System.

Software Requirements

CASE Tool: StarUML / Visual Paradigm (Community Edition)

Operating System: Windows / macOS / Linux

System Type: UML Modeling Tool

Tool Selected

StarUML / Visual Paradigm

Procedure
Step 1: Installation

Download StarUML or Visual Paradigm from the official website.

Run the installer and follow the on-screen instructions.

Launch the application after successful installation.

Step 2: Project Creation

Open the CASE tool.

Select File → New Project.

Choose UML Modeling.

Name the project as Predictive Stock Management System.

Step 3: Diagram Configuration

The following UML diagrams were created to model the system:

Use Case Diagram

Actors: Admin, Store Manager

Use Cases: Predict Stock Demand, Manage Inventory, Generate Reports

Class Diagram

Classes: Product, Inventory, SalesData, PredictionModel, User

Sequence Diagram

Interaction between Sales Data, Prediction Model, and Inventory Module

Activity Diagram

Workflow of stock monitoring and replenishment

Step 4: System Modules Defined

Stock Prediction Module

Inventory Management Module

Sales Analysis Module

Reporting Module

Step 5: Saving and Exporting

Save the project file in the tool’s default format.

Export diagrams in PDF/PNG format for documentation and submission.

Result

The CASE tool was successfully installed and configured. UML diagrams for the Predictive Stock Management System were created and saved, enabling effective system modeling and documentation.

Conclusion

Using a CASE tool simplifies system design by providing structured UML diagrams. The Predictive Stock Management System was effectively modeled using standard UML techniques.
